Assignment 1

Dataset : NESARC codebook 

Research question: Is depression and social phobia a biproduct of alcoholism or cause?

Introduction :The U.S. National Epidemiological Survey on Alcohol and Related Conditions (NESARC) is a survey designed to determine the magnitude of alcohol use and psychiatric disorders in the U.S. population. It is a representative sample of the non-institutionalized population 18 years and older.

Abstract : Aims is to examine the given dataset and find the associations between alcohol use disorders (AUD),major depression (MD) and Social phobia to evaluate the evidence for the existence of a causal relationship between the disorders.

Items included in the CodeBook: 
main focus on the data given in
- SECTION 4A: MAJOR DEPRESSION (LOW MOOD I)
- SECTION 7: SOCIAL PHOBIA (SOCIAL SITUATIONS)

along with contents given in
-SECTION 4B: FAMILY HISTORY (III) OF MAJOR DEPRESSION
-SECTION 4C: DYSTHYMIA (LOW MOOD II)

Literature Review:
1. Alcohol and depression by Joseph M. Boden  David M. Fergusson
(https://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/abs/10.1111/j.1360-0443.2010.03351.x)
2.Social phobia and alcoholism: a complex relationship by Jean-PierreLépineAntoinePélissolo
(https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/abs/pii/S0165032798000895)

Summary:
Saddness and anxiety can be a driving forcus for alcoholism.
This will be my attempt to check the correration between depression,social phobia and alcoholism.
